1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:04,295
[brazen music playing]

2
00:00:10,969 --> 00:00:15,056
[electronic blipping]

3
00:00:17,934 --> 00:00:19,728
[Delfin] <i>You're the one</i>
<i>who brought the statue back.</i>

4
00:00:19,811 --> 00:00:21,020
Were you involved
in the incident at the port…

5
00:00:21,104 --> 00:00:22,147
PREVIOUSLY

6
00:00:22,230 --> 00:00:24,733
<i>…and the container van?</i>

7
00:00:24,816 --> 00:00:26,568
[Red] <i>By the way, I've already set people</i>

8
00:00:26,651 --> 00:00:29,112
<i>on finding out who caused our setback.</i>

9
00:00:29,195 --> 00:00:32,949
[Delfin] <i>Thanks to Saint Anthony,</i>
<i>you made it back safely.</i>

10
00:00:33,450 --> 00:00:35,702
[Atoy] <i>I wonder if he could</i>
<i>restore your health too.</i>

11
00:00:36,494 --> 00:00:37,871
[Delfin] <i>Do you still have the skill?</i>

12
00:00:37,954 --> 00:00:39,414
<i>Make me a new suit.</i>

13
00:00:39,497 --> 00:00:40,623
I'll pick the fabric myself.

14
00:00:40,707 --> 00:00:42,125
Are you heading somewhere?

15
00:00:42,208 --> 00:00:43,835
[Delfin] <i>It's about time</i>
<i>you get some practice.</i>

16
00:00:43,918 --> 00:00:45,044
<i>You see,</i>

17
00:00:45,128 --> 00:00:49,132
<i>I believe everyone</i>
<i>should have a proper suit</i>

18
00:00:49,215 --> 00:00:52,302
<i>as a reminder that we are all unique</i>

19
00:00:52,802 --> 00:00:54,554
and beautifully tailor-made by God.

20
00:00:54,637 --> 00:00:58,224
He's got a lead on the idiot
who interfered with our operations.

21
00:00:58,308 --> 00:01:00,185
Who is it? And why are you
only telling me this now?

22
00:01:00,268 --> 00:01:01,811
[Paldo] <i>He's our tailor's son.</i>

23
00:01:01,895 --> 00:01:03,480
<i>His name is Atoy.</i>

24
00:01:03,563 --> 00:01:04,731
[Red] <i>Where can I find this Atoy?</i>

25
00:01:04,814 --> 00:01:06,691
Look. That's him.

26
00:01:06,775 --> 00:01:09,110
[brazen music continues]

27
00:01:09,194 --> 00:01:10,779
[care engine revving]

28
00:01:10,862 --> 00:01:11,780
[brake squeals]

29
00:01:12,989 --> 00:01:15,825
[overlapping chattering, screaming]

30
00:01:15,909 --> 00:01:17,952
[Atoy] Please send help!
I'm begging you, please, hurry!

31
00:01:18,036 --> 00:01:19,996
[Paldo] <i>Sir, I think you might</i>
<i>have killed Atoy's father.</i>

32
00:01:21,247 --> 00:01:22,457
<i>He didn't do anything wrong.</i>

33
00:01:22,540 --> 00:01:24,083
[Red] <i>Serves him right.</i>

34
00:01:24,167 --> 00:01:25,919
His life is the price
of his son's mistakes.

35
00:01:26,002 --> 00:01:28,963
[brazen music concludes]

36
00:01:46,189 --> 00:01:48,066
[background scuffling]

37
00:01:49,818 --> 00:01:52,278
Now you can rest in peace
before Saint Peter

38
00:01:52,362 --> 00:01:54,531
and Mom in heaven, looking handsome
in the suit I made for you.

39
00:01:56,241 --> 00:01:57,659
[somber music playing]

40
00:01:57,742 --> 00:02:00,036
[chain jingles]

41
00:02:16,511 --> 00:02:18,054
[indistinct chattering]

42
00:02:20,181 --> 00:02:22,684
Atoy, my condolences.

43
00:02:24,686 --> 00:02:26,187
- Thank you. I appreciate it.
- [muttering]

44
00:02:26,271 --> 00:02:28,148
- [Bunda] My condolences, Atoy.
- [woman] My condolences, Atoy.

45
00:02:53,006 --> 00:02:55,133
[background sniffling]

46
00:03:10,940 --> 00:03:15,862
[somber music intensifies]

47
00:03:36,758 --> 00:03:37,717
[sobs]

48
00:03:38,927 --> 00:03:41,679
[sobbing]

49
00:03:44,724 --> 00:03:46,476
[sobbing]

50
00:03:51,606 --> 00:03:55,026
[sobbing]

51
00:03:55,109 --> 00:03:57,070
Hey, I thought you were
all tough and fearless?

52
00:03:58,112 --> 00:03:59,572
[sobbing]

53
00:03:59,656 --> 00:04:05,620
Atoy, I'm going to miss Sir Delfin.

54
00:04:06,204 --> 00:04:08,498
[Cita] There, there.

55
00:04:08,581 --> 00:04:09,540
[sobbing]

56
00:04:09,624 --> 00:04:10,458
[sniffles]

57
00:04:10,541 --> 00:04:16,172
I still don't understand
why this had to happen to Delfin.

58
00:04:16,256 --> 00:04:18,258
His days were already numbered.

59
00:04:18,341 --> 00:04:20,593
[Karla sobbing]

60
00:04:20,677 --> 00:04:24,097
I hope lightning strikes
whoever ran Delfin over!

61
00:04:24,180 --> 00:04:25,556
He's a monster! A monster!

62
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:27,684
- [Nestor] A monster, I tell you!
- [sinister music playing]

63
00:04:27,767 --> 00:04:28,851
He's a monster!

64
00:04:29,978 --> 00:04:32,230
[shushes]

65
00:04:32,313 --> 00:04:33,273
Father.

66
00:04:35,066 --> 00:04:37,568
- [sobbing]
- [somber music playing]

67
00:04:39,445 --> 00:04:40,280
[Peping clears throat]

68
00:04:40,363 --> 00:04:43,408
[sobbing]

69
00:04:49,747 --> 00:04:51,207
[Peping] My condolences, Atoy.

70
00:04:51,958 --> 00:04:55,670
We will continue to pray
at the parish for Delfin's soul

71
00:04:56,170 --> 00:04:57,714
and for justice to be served.

72
00:04:57,797 --> 00:04:59,382
Thank you, Father.

73
00:05:08,182 --> 00:05:11,227
Do we already have any leads
on who that madman is?

74
00:05:11,311 --> 00:05:15,481
[pensive music playing]

75
00:05:21,279 --> 00:05:22,405
[clears throat]

76
00:05:27,035 --> 00:05:28,161
[Ranger clears throat]

77
00:05:28,745 --> 00:05:29,662
Sir.

78
00:05:38,546 --> 00:05:42,633
[stirring music playing]

79
00:05:44,385 --> 00:05:45,511
[door squeaks open]

80
00:05:49,390 --> 00:05:51,350
[suave music playing]

81
00:05:51,434 --> 00:05:53,102
FATHER'S LANE
FOOD HUB IN BACLARAN

82
00:05:56,731 --> 00:05:57,857
[swishing]

83
00:06:00,985 --> 00:06:03,696
[sewing machine whirring]

84
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:05,239
[swishing]

85
00:06:05,323 --> 00:06:07,200
[snipping]

86
00:06:35,645 --> 00:06:39,607
This is the area where your father
was struck, Captain.

87
00:06:39,690 --> 00:06:42,568
This is the final confirmed sighting
from our informant.

88
00:06:42,652 --> 00:06:44,987
There are no CCTV cameras
at the end of the street,

89
00:06:45,071 --> 00:06:48,116
but it leads to a dead end anyway.

90
00:06:50,701 --> 00:06:51,911
Where exactly is this place, sir?

91
00:06:51,994 --> 00:06:53,162
I'll go there myself.

92
00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:55,706
I asked the team to make a sweep.

93
00:06:55,790 --> 00:07:00,419
There were three black cars parked
along that entire stretch of road.

94
00:07:01,129 --> 00:07:04,048
They're different models,
and each one has a plate number.

95
00:07:04,132 --> 00:07:07,718
[in English] The car that we're
searching for is not one of them.

96
00:07:08,302 --> 00:07:09,929
[in English] Even the residents there

97
00:07:10,596 --> 00:07:13,224
don't have any idea
about the car we're looking for.

98
00:07:13,307 --> 00:07:16,436
No cars were parked there,
and no one saw anything.

99
00:07:16,519 --> 00:07:19,856
It's like the car
just vanished into thin air.

100
00:07:19,939 --> 00:07:21,524
- [chair clacks]
- That's impossible!

101
00:07:21,607 --> 00:07:22,817
- [chair clacks]
- Completely impossible!

102
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:25,069
It's impossible for it
to just disappear like that!

103
00:07:25,653 --> 00:07:28,030
[scoffs] Sir, give me all the details.

104
00:07:28,114 --> 00:07:29,490
I'm going to find that bastard myself!

105
00:07:29,574 --> 00:07:32,201
Sir, it's impossible for that car
to just vanish into thin air!

106
00:07:32,285 --> 00:07:33,661
I will eventually find it.

107
00:07:34,245 --> 00:07:36,497
[in English] We all know
that sometimes they do,

108
00:07:36,581 --> 00:07:38,624
whether it's a thing or a person.

109
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:39,917
And sometimes,

110
00:07:40,418 --> 00:07:42,044
it really does take
a long time to find them.

111
00:07:42,128 --> 00:07:45,214
Especially if they're deliberately hiding
or being hidden.

112
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:48,342
[inhales] I can still do this.
I've got this.

113
00:07:50,011 --> 00:07:53,514
- [pensive music playing]
- [Ranger sighs]

114
00:07:55,766 --> 00:07:58,686
[in English] Have you thought
of your next plan, Captain?

115
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:03,024
[in English] Will you be managing
this shop?

116
00:08:03,107 --> 00:08:07,320
Or… are you going back to work?

117
00:08:08,529 --> 00:08:11,866
I also heard about the chaos
at the port a few weeks ago.

118
00:08:12,450 --> 00:08:16,454
I don't need an intel report
to tell me that it was you

119
00:08:17,163 --> 00:08:21,250
making another successful
retrieval operation.

120
00:08:22,043 --> 00:08:23,669
It was a personal mission, sir.

121
00:08:24,879 --> 00:08:28,508
That saint was very important to me.

122
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:30,384
And not just to me,

123
00:08:30,468 --> 00:08:34,889
but to my community and my father as well.

124
00:08:35,932 --> 00:08:37,433
[in English] No need to explain.

125
00:08:37,517 --> 00:08:39,268
[in English] I just wanted to commend you.

126
00:08:39,894 --> 00:08:43,481
[in English] Because even after months
of no assignment,

127
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:46,651
you still got the skills.

128
00:08:46,734 --> 00:08:50,154
- [sighs]
- [in English] Well, you've always had it.

129
00:08:50,238 --> 00:08:51,155
Uh…

130
00:08:51,239 --> 00:08:56,202
You know how much I trust your abilities.

131
00:08:56,285 --> 00:08:58,412
It would be a waste to let them go unused.

132
00:08:59,038 --> 00:09:00,540
Maybe…

133
00:09:01,916 --> 00:09:05,795
[in English] Can you still
take on special jobs for me?

134
00:09:08,506 --> 00:09:09,632
Get ready.

135
00:09:09,715 --> 00:09:10,550
[Atoy murmurs]

136
00:09:10,633 --> 00:09:12,468
You'll have to carry this on
once I'm gone, all right?

137
00:09:14,887 --> 00:09:16,305
I'm sorry, sir.

138
00:09:16,389 --> 00:09:18,224
I can't make any promises right now.

139
00:09:18,307 --> 00:09:23,479
Especially now, I already have my hands
full with orders here at the shop.

140
00:09:23,563 --> 00:09:24,730
And besides,

141
00:09:25,648 --> 00:09:30,194
it's my father's dream for me…
to inherit this place.

142
00:09:32,363 --> 00:09:33,948
[exhales sharply]

143
00:09:34,448 --> 00:09:35,950
[in English] Think it over.

144
00:09:37,326 --> 00:09:38,869
Again, my condolences,

145
00:09:39,370 --> 00:09:40,454
Padua.

146
00:09:40,538 --> 00:09:41,622
Thank you, sir.

147
00:09:41,706 --> 00:09:46,711
- [melancholic music playing]
- [long exhale]

148
00:09:56,262 --> 00:09:57,555
[Atoy clicks tongue] Son of a thread!

149
00:09:57,638 --> 00:09:59,515
Can you please stop moving so much?

150
00:09:59,599 --> 00:10:00,558
[in English] Steady.

151
00:10:04,812 --> 00:10:06,314
[clicks tongue] I said stay still!
What gives?

152
00:10:06,397 --> 00:10:07,732
Darn it, the marking's gone!

153
00:10:07,815 --> 00:10:09,859
What exactly do you want?
Are we still doing this or not?!

154
00:10:09,942 --> 00:10:13,154
You could've just said it
clearly and calmly.

155
00:10:13,237 --> 00:10:14,071
Calmly?

156
00:10:14,155 --> 00:10:16,282
If you want calm, go have
your suit tailored by a priest.

157
00:10:16,365 --> 00:10:19,327
If you want something even calmer,
go to a corpse!

158
00:10:20,077 --> 00:10:21,579
Tell me. Are we still doing this or what?

159
00:10:23,164 --> 00:10:24,165
Yes.

160
00:10:24,248 --> 00:10:26,667
[tense music playing]

161
00:10:27,251 --> 00:10:28,669
- [in English] Twenty-three.
- [Cita] Twenty-three.

162
00:10:28,753 --> 00:10:31,005
Let's cut it down by two.
It's gotten too long.

163
00:10:34,175 --> 00:10:36,677
- [bright music playing]
- [chimes]

164
00:10:37,261 --> 00:10:38,262
Oh.

165
00:10:38,804 --> 00:10:40,765
Please have a seat for a moment.
I'll be right back.

166
00:10:40,848 --> 00:10:41,807
- Thank you.
- Okay.

167
00:10:42,516 --> 00:10:43,517
Where is Karla?

168
00:10:43,601 --> 00:10:45,353
I asked her to come and help.

169
00:10:45,436 --> 00:10:47,688
She's probably still out skateboarding.

170
00:10:48,189 --> 00:10:49,732
Wait, has her skateboard been fixed?

171
00:10:49,815 --> 00:10:51,609
- [exciting music playing]
- [man] Hey!

172
00:10:51,692 --> 00:10:52,610
[Karla] Oops!

173
00:10:52,693 --> 00:10:53,527
- [Karla] Excuse me!
- [Bunda] Yeah.

174
00:10:53,611 --> 00:10:55,154
- [Bunda] Lower!
- [Karla] Excuse me, sir!

175
00:10:55,237 --> 00:10:59,075
[squealing]

176
00:10:59,158 --> 00:11:00,826
[Karla] Sorry, Auntie Bunda!

177
00:11:00,910 --> 00:11:03,496
- [clamoring]
- [Paldo gasps] Oh!

178
00:11:03,579 --> 00:11:05,873
Karla! Can you please watch it?!
This kid, I swear!

179
00:11:05,956 --> 00:11:08,209
[Karla] I'm sorry!
My skateboard is acting up!

180
00:11:09,752 --> 00:11:10,836
[Cita] Atoy! Atoy!

181
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:13,547
- Yes?
- Add this to the list.

182
00:11:15,132 --> 00:11:17,343
- Wow, there's so much.
- And this one too.

183
00:11:17,426 --> 00:11:18,552
- [wheels scraping]
- Hey! Hey!

184
00:11:18,636 --> 00:11:19,678
Hey, Karla!

185
00:11:19,762 --> 00:11:20,930
[exciting music continues]

186
00:11:21,013 --> 00:11:22,139
[Karla] Emerson, move aside!

187
00:11:22,223 --> 00:11:24,850
- [screams, grunts]
- [Karla shrieks]

188
00:11:24,934 --> 00:11:26,560
Emerson. [grunts]

189
00:11:27,144 --> 00:11:28,270
- I'm sorry! My bad!
- Hey!

190
00:11:28,354 --> 00:11:29,855
Hey! My goodness!

191
00:11:29,939 --> 00:11:31,065
Emerson, I'm sorry.

192
00:11:31,148 --> 00:11:32,942
Don't touch it! Don't touch it!

193
00:11:33,025 --> 00:11:34,235
- I'm sorry!
- For the love of God!

194
00:11:34,318 --> 00:11:35,403
- I'm sorry! I really am!
- Watch it!

195
00:11:35,486 --> 00:11:37,530
[Emerson] You're ruining everything!

196
00:11:37,613 --> 00:11:39,115
What's wrong with you, Karla?!

197
00:11:39,198 --> 00:11:40,241
I'm really sorry!

198
00:11:40,741 --> 00:11:42,284
- [Emerson] Look what you've done!
- [Cita] Karla!

199
00:11:42,368 --> 00:11:43,953
- [Emerson] You should be more careful.
- What?

200
00:11:44,036 --> 00:11:44,870
[inhales]

201
00:11:44,954 --> 00:11:46,205
My goodness!

202
00:11:46,288 --> 00:11:48,249
This is all your fault!
You better pay for this!

203
00:11:48,332 --> 00:11:50,292
Karla, what have you done this time?

204
00:11:50,376 --> 00:11:52,628
I already told you
not to use that skateboard!

205
00:11:52,711 --> 00:11:54,797
- Now you've caused trouble again!
- I was actually trying to fix it.

206
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:57,258
- Quit making excuses!
- [Cita] You're just making this worse.

207
00:11:57,341 --> 00:11:59,385
- [Emerson] What now?
- Where are you going to get the money?

208
00:11:59,468 --> 00:12:01,345
Emerson's asking you to pay.
Your dad won't be able to help you.

209
00:12:01,429 --> 00:12:03,848
I'm sure he's going to scold you again!

210
00:12:03,931 --> 00:12:05,015
[Emerson] What a nuisance!

211
00:12:05,099 --> 00:12:06,642
Someone's gotta pay for this!

212
00:12:07,393 --> 00:12:08,769
How much does she owe you?
I'll pay for it instead.

213
00:12:08,853 --> 00:12:10,813
- Just put it on my tab.
- No can do.

214
00:12:10,896 --> 00:12:12,231
I need to have this
delivered this right now.

215
00:12:12,314 --> 00:12:14,608
- This is ridiculous.
- [Paldo] What is going on here?

216
00:12:14,692 --> 00:12:15,901
- [Emerson mutters]
- What's all the fuss about?

217
00:12:15,985 --> 00:12:17,820
She's to blame. Just the other day,

218
00:12:17,903 --> 00:12:20,072
you broke Sir Jojo's eggs.

219
00:12:20,156 --> 00:12:22,491
And now, you've done it again
and made this dirty!

220
00:12:22,575 --> 00:12:24,660
Is causing trouble
your hobby or something?

221
00:12:24,743 --> 00:12:26,203
Sir, I'll have to file a blotter report
to put a stop to this.

222
00:12:26,287 --> 00:12:27,288
- [Karla] Just a moment, Emerson!
- Huh-uh…

223
00:12:27,371 --> 00:12:28,414
Please don't.

224
00:12:28,497 --> 00:12:29,623
I already said I'll pay for it!

225
00:12:29,707 --> 00:12:30,916
As you should.

226
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:33,210
- [Paldo] What happened here?
- Anyway, I'll go ahead now.

227
00:12:33,294 --> 00:12:34,211
- Karla, where do you think you're going?
- [Karla] Bye.

228
00:12:34,295 --> 00:12:36,714
- We need to talk!
- Don't worry, I'll handle this.

229
00:12:36,797 --> 00:12:37,923
[Atoy] Leave it to me.

230
00:12:38,007 --> 00:12:39,675
I told you to help me out in the shop.

231
00:12:39,758 --> 00:12:40,926
- [Karla] But I was already running late!
- [Emerson] Oh…

232
00:12:41,010 --> 00:12:42,344
[Emerson] You have to pay for it!

233
00:12:42,428 --> 00:12:43,387
Karla!

234
00:12:43,471 --> 00:12:44,346
[Paldo] Just take it easy.

235
00:12:44,430 --> 00:12:45,389
- You need to calm down.
- [whines]

236
00:12:45,473 --> 00:12:46,682
But I really need

237
00:12:46,765 --> 00:12:47,892
to make this delivery.

238
00:12:47,975 --> 00:12:49,143
‪[whimsical music playing]

239
00:12:52,021 --> 00:12:53,189
Hey, Karla.

240
00:12:53,898 --> 00:12:55,149
We need to talk.

241
00:12:55,232 --> 00:12:56,609
I still have to go to school.

242
00:12:56,692 --> 00:12:58,235
You're just going to lecture me anyway.

243
00:12:58,319 --> 00:12:59,153
[water splashes]

244
00:12:59,236 --> 00:13:00,696
Wow, you're heading to school
dressed like that?

245
00:13:00,779 --> 00:13:01,697
You're not even in your uniform.

246
00:13:01,780 --> 00:13:03,032
[shushes]

247
00:13:03,991 --> 00:13:05,659
I'm still talking to you.
Don't turn your back on me.

248
00:13:05,743 --> 00:13:07,036
Don't you dare walk away from me.

249
00:13:07,119 --> 00:13:08,579
[somber music playing]

250
00:13:11,540 --> 00:13:12,833
What's going on with you?

251
00:13:14,126 --> 00:13:16,128
Why do you keep getting worse and worse?

252
00:13:16,962 --> 00:13:20,090
When you were younger,
you were already sneaking money.

253
00:13:20,174 --> 00:13:23,844
And now you're causing trouble everywhere,
even talking back to your own mother.

254
00:13:23,928 --> 00:13:25,971
What's happening to you?
You're getting more immature by the day!

255
00:13:26,555 --> 00:13:29,683
If I were your parent,
I'd be upset with you too.

256
00:13:32,436 --> 00:13:34,605
And Mom isn't any different.
She hasn't changed at all!

257
00:13:34,688 --> 00:13:35,773
What do you mean?

258
00:13:35,856 --> 00:13:37,024
Miss Cita is a good person.

259
00:13:37,107 --> 00:13:38,609
What exactly do you have
against your mother?

260
00:13:40,152 --> 00:13:42,863
Forget it. You wouldn't understand anyway.

261
00:13:44,198 --> 00:13:46,492
How am I supposed to understand
if you won't tell me?

262
00:13:49,537 --> 00:13:50,496
Karla.

263
00:13:51,872 --> 00:13:54,750
Holding a grudge against
your own parents isn't good.

264
00:13:54,833 --> 00:13:55,709
Keep that in mind.

265
00:13:57,002 --> 00:13:58,420
Nothing good will come out of it.

266
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:01,298
Believe me.

267
00:14:01,799 --> 00:14:05,594
[somber music continues]

268
00:14:05,678 --> 00:14:06,720
Whatever.

269
00:14:06,804 --> 00:14:07,888
- Not so fast!
- [Karla] I'm leaving.

270
00:14:10,724 --> 00:14:14,186
Do you want to make some money,

271
00:14:15,020 --> 00:14:17,731
so you can pay Emerson back
for the trouble you caused?

272
00:14:18,983 --> 00:14:21,610
Come with me. I've got a side gig for you.

273
00:14:22,820 --> 00:14:23,821
Let's go.

274
00:14:23,904 --> 00:14:26,657
- [funky music playing]
- [clicks tongue]

275
00:14:26,740 --> 00:14:27,992
[Atoy] Come on!

276
00:14:28,701 --> 00:14:29,743
[Karla] Atoy.

277
00:14:31,161 --> 00:14:33,330
Why don't you just
help out at the shop instead?

278
00:14:33,414 --> 00:14:35,249
- We actually need an assistant there.
- [man shouts]

279
00:14:35,332 --> 00:14:36,750
Master Cutter!

280
00:14:36,834 --> 00:14:38,002
You forgot this.

281
00:14:38,085 --> 00:14:38,961
Oh, thank you!

282
00:14:39,044 --> 00:14:40,170
- No problem. See you around.
- Take care!

283
00:14:41,046 --> 00:14:42,673
Your mom could use some help.

284
00:14:42,756 --> 00:14:45,175
She needs an assistant.
And I could use an assistant as well.

285
00:14:45,259 --> 00:14:46,302
Come on!

286
00:14:46,385 --> 00:14:47,595
Fine!

287
00:14:48,095 --> 00:14:49,388
I'll keep an eye on the shop.

288
00:14:50,055 --> 00:14:51,348
And only when I'm free, okay?

289
00:14:51,432 --> 00:14:53,559
[scoffs] Now that's
what I'm talking about.

290
00:14:53,642 --> 00:14:57,146
Why didn't you just say yes
to your mom the first time she asked you?

291
00:14:57,229 --> 00:14:59,523
I can't believe
you made me ask you instead.

292
00:15:00,733 --> 00:15:02,067
Well, you actually scare me!

293
00:15:02,151 --> 00:15:03,152
[scoffs]

294
00:15:04,236 --> 00:15:05,613
[Atoy] I'm glad you finally said yes.

295
00:15:05,696 --> 00:15:06,822
Do you want to start now?

296
00:15:11,452 --> 00:15:13,662
Fruid drinks! Banana cue!

297
00:15:13,746 --> 00:15:15,331
Rice cakes!

298
00:15:15,414 --> 00:15:17,458
- [Atoy huffs] Hey.
- We've got banana cue here!

299
00:15:17,541 --> 00:15:19,543
[Karla] Wow. Can you please treat us
to some drinks?

300
00:15:19,627 --> 00:15:21,420
Wait, I don't think I have any change.

301
00:15:21,503 --> 00:15:23,714
Oh. Not a problem.
We accept bank transfer here.

302
00:15:23,797 --> 00:15:25,716
Bank transfer? Fancy!

303
00:15:25,799 --> 00:15:27,801
Fine! It's on me.

304
00:15:27,885 --> 00:15:30,596
Give me two fruid drinks
and one rice cake.

305
00:15:30,679 --> 00:15:32,014
- One for me.
- I'd like two rice cakes.

306
00:15:32,598 --> 00:15:33,724
And one banana cue.

307
00:15:33,807 --> 00:15:36,977
[funky music playing]

308
00:15:37,061 --> 00:15:38,938
And maybe add one more of this.

309
00:15:40,064 --> 00:15:41,273
Hey!

310
00:15:41,357 --> 00:15:42,691
Give me my phone back!

311
00:15:43,275 --> 00:15:44,360
Huh?

312
00:15:49,365 --> 00:15:51,450
Oh my! I need to call the police!

313
00:15:51,533 --> 00:15:53,702
Please keep an eye
on my things for a second!

314
00:15:53,786 --> 00:15:56,956
[mischievous music playing]

315
00:16:00,709 --> 00:16:01,710
Hey!

316
00:16:02,211 --> 00:16:03,128
Are you the thief?

317
00:16:03,754 --> 00:16:06,382
Huh? Do I look like a thief to you?

318
00:16:07,174 --> 00:16:08,300
You know what?

319
00:16:08,384 --> 00:16:10,594
You're handsome, but it's a shame
you're so judgmental!

320
00:16:10,678 --> 00:16:12,304
Miss, I'm sorry,
but someone stole my phone.

321
00:16:12,388 --> 00:16:13,847
Did you happen to see anyone pass by here?

322
00:16:14,431 --> 00:16:18,644
- Well, I did see a guy running earlier.
- [cock crowing]

323
00:16:18,727 --> 00:16:20,354
He went that way!

324
00:16:21,063 --> 00:16:22,898
- No wonder he was in such a hurry.
- [Karla] Thank you so much!

325
00:16:22,982 --> 00:16:25,651
[whimsical music playing]

326
00:16:26,902 --> 00:16:27,736
[Ame] What are you staring at?

327
00:16:27,820 --> 00:16:30,406
Don't tell me you've never seen
a little person before?

328
00:16:30,489 --> 00:16:34,868
[whimsical music continues]

329
00:16:44,378 --> 00:16:45,963
Hey, Ame!

330
00:16:46,463 --> 00:16:47,965
You didn't get caught by those two?

331
00:16:48,048 --> 00:16:50,551
Of course not. I'm actually
a pretty great actress!

332
00:16:51,301 --> 00:16:54,096
I wonder how much
Sir John is going to pay us.

333
00:16:54,179 --> 00:16:55,556
We're definitely getting
a huge amount for this.

334
00:16:56,932 --> 00:16:59,476
[Atoy] I knew it.
"Small but terrible" is true after all.

335
00:17:01,562 --> 00:17:03,063
And double the trouble at that!

336
00:17:04,231 --> 00:17:07,818
[mischievous music playing]

337
00:17:07,901 --> 00:17:09,820
I knew it. You were lying.

338
00:17:10,654 --> 00:17:13,240
[Atoy] <i>I saw your footprints</i>
<i>over by the leaves.</i>

339
00:17:13,323 --> 00:17:16,035
And the chair you used.
You tried to hide it, but I noticed.

340
00:17:16,577 --> 00:17:17,536
Hey!

341
00:17:22,207 --> 00:17:23,292
[Atoy] And most of all,

342
00:17:23,375 --> 00:17:24,543
- those bracelets
- [Ibyang] Banana cue!

343
00:17:24,626 --> 00:17:26,420
<i>you're wearing are clearly identical.</i>

344
00:17:26,503 --> 00:17:28,297
Are you two working together?

345
00:17:28,380 --> 00:17:30,507
You’re so small, and yet--

346
00:17:30,591 --> 00:17:31,633
Do you have something
against little people?

347
00:17:32,426 --> 00:17:33,677
[playful music playing]

348
00:17:33,761 --> 00:17:35,429
You're still a child, and yet
you're already so rebellious!

349
00:17:38,390 --> 00:17:39,933
- Hey!
- Stop!

350
00:17:40,017 --> 00:17:41,602
- That's mine!
- Hey, psst!

351
00:17:41,685 --> 00:17:43,353
- This isn't yours. This belongs to Karla.
- [muttering]

352
00:17:43,437 --> 00:17:44,605
- That's mine!
- I don't think so. This is Karla's.

353
00:17:44,688 --> 00:17:45,898
- What are you talking about?
- That's ours-

354
00:17:45,981 --> 00:17:47,107
How are you related to this child,

355
00:17:47,191 --> 00:17:49,318
and why are you allowing her
to wander the streets?

356
00:17:49,401 --> 00:17:52,237
- Nothing you say can hurt or offend me.
- Just give it back already!

357
00:17:52,321 --> 00:17:53,781
Stop it, kid!

358
00:17:53,864 --> 00:17:55,824
- This is unbelievable.
- Kids like you should be at home instead.

359
00:17:55,908 --> 00:17:56,992
[Ame] Give it back!

360
00:17:57,076 --> 00:17:58,202
[siren blaring in distance]

361
00:17:58,285 --> 00:17:59,745
Hey, give it to me!

362
00:17:59,828 --> 00:18:02,247
If you don't give the phone back,

363
00:18:02,331 --> 00:18:04,249
I'm dropping this.

364
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:05,793
Really now?

365
00:18:05,876 --> 00:18:07,044
Fine, if you won't give it back,

366
00:18:07,127 --> 00:18:09,671
I'll just tell your father instead!
He's going to spank you for sure!

367
00:18:09,755 --> 00:18:11,381
Whatever!

368
00:18:11,465 --> 00:18:13,092
I don't have a father.

369
00:18:13,175 --> 00:18:14,134
But as for you,

370
00:18:14,718 --> 00:18:17,179
why don't you just go home
to your wife and kids?

371
00:18:17,262 --> 00:18:18,847
Leave us alone already!

372
00:18:18,931 --> 00:18:21,141
Hey, I'm very much single,

373
00:18:21,225 --> 00:18:24,186
so I've got all the time in the world
to deal with kids like you!

374
00:18:24,269 --> 00:18:26,605
If you don't return that to me,
I'll call the police.

375
00:18:27,272 --> 00:18:28,982
Go ahead. It's empty anyway.

376
00:18:31,819 --> 00:18:32,694
Hey!

377
00:18:34,071 --> 00:18:35,364
- Ibyang, run!
- [Ibyang] Mm.

378
00:18:35,447 --> 00:18:37,783
- [brazen music playing]
- [Atoy] Oh!

379
00:18:58,387 --> 00:18:59,847
Atoy, why did you jump in?!

380
00:18:59,930 --> 00:19:02,057
For crying out loud!

381
00:19:04,059 --> 00:19:05,811
I almost got your phone back

382
00:19:06,520 --> 00:19:08,689
from those two little girls who stole it!

383
00:19:09,189 --> 00:19:10,691
Who are you referring to?

384
00:19:10,774 --> 00:19:12,776
The child selling rice cakes

385
00:19:12,860 --> 00:19:15,737
and the girl behind her,
the small one too!

386
00:19:15,821 --> 00:19:17,239
Seriously?!

387
00:19:17,322 --> 00:19:19,575
I can't believe she's an accomplice!

388
00:19:19,658 --> 00:19:20,492
[whimsical music playing]

389
00:19:20,576 --> 00:19:21,785
Looks can be deceiving!

390
00:19:21,869 --> 00:19:23,954
She looked so sweet and innocent!

391
00:19:24,037 --> 00:19:25,164
Little did I know she was a thief.

392
00:19:25,247 --> 00:19:26,456
Atoy, we have to go get them.

393
00:19:26,540 --> 00:19:27,875
They're gone.

394
00:19:28,375 --> 00:19:30,252
They're definitely hiding as we speak
after being exposed

395
00:19:31,128 --> 00:19:32,212
and caught red-handed like that.

396
00:19:33,463 --> 00:19:35,924
If I ever see those two again,
I'm going to make them pay.

397
00:19:36,925 --> 00:19:38,260
- Let's go!
- [clicks tongue]

398
00:19:39,011 --> 00:19:40,012
Such a bummer!

399
00:19:41,471 --> 00:19:43,974
I had so many photos on that phone
that weren't backed up.

400
00:19:44,474 --> 00:19:45,976
- [Atoy] Hmm.
- I have no means to buy a new phone.

401
00:19:46,059 --> 00:19:47,352
I'm broke.

402
00:19:47,436 --> 00:19:49,188
Mom's going to get upset at me for sure.

403
00:19:49,271 --> 00:19:52,524
You should stop resisting and just agree
to be an assistant in my shop,

404
00:19:52,608 --> 00:19:53,984
so you can buy a new phone.

405
00:19:54,067 --> 00:19:55,319
Atoy, I really don't want to.

406
00:19:55,402 --> 00:19:56,778
- [groans] But your job will be easy.
- I'm sorry, but I refuse.

407
00:19:56,862 --> 00:19:57,696
I have nothing against you.

408
00:19:57,779 --> 00:19:59,364
It's just that there's someone
in that shop I don't want to see.

409
00:19:59,448 --> 00:20:01,533
You know who I mean.

410
00:20:02,034 --> 00:20:03,285
- [mumbles]
- Excuse me.

411
00:20:03,368 --> 00:20:05,871
Do you know the directions
to Sir Delfin's shop?

412
00:20:05,954 --> 00:20:06,997
Oh, he owns that shop.

413
00:20:07,080 --> 00:20:09,041
Are you Master Cutter Atoy?

414
00:20:09,124 --> 00:20:11,043
- Yes, that's me.
- Perfect timing.

415
00:20:11,126 --> 00:20:13,420
Can I have this suit altered?

416
00:20:14,713 --> 00:20:15,631
Let me see.

417
00:20:15,714 --> 00:20:17,132
Mmm-hmm.

418
00:20:17,216 --> 00:20:18,091
No problem.

419
00:20:18,175 --> 00:20:19,134
Just bring it to the shop.

420
00:20:19,218 --> 00:20:20,427
- Awesome. Thank you so much.
- I can even make you a new one.

421
00:20:20,510 --> 00:20:21,595
[Emerson] Hey…!

422
00:20:21,678 --> 00:20:23,180
Not so fast. Stop it. Stop right there!

423
00:20:23,931 --> 00:20:24,973
Atoy.

424
00:20:25,057 --> 00:20:25,933
[whimsical music playing]

425
00:20:26,016 --> 00:20:28,852
I know exactly what you're trying to do.
You're stealing my client.

426
00:20:29,353 --> 00:20:31,355
What are you talking about?
He was the one who came up to me.

427
00:20:32,022 --> 00:20:33,565
Drop the act. Stop lying.

428
00:20:33,649 --> 00:20:35,442
Don't lie to me, Atoy. I'm not buying it.

429
00:20:35,525 --> 00:20:37,945
You-- Sir… Mr. Velasco.

430
00:20:38,737 --> 00:20:40,989
What exactly did this guy tell you? Huh?

431
00:20:41,073 --> 00:20:43,158
[titters] Did he promise you a discount?

432
00:20:43,242 --> 00:20:44,576
Oh my, don't believe a word he says.

433
00:20:44,660 --> 00:20:45,535
He'll say everything
just to steal customers!

434
00:20:45,619 --> 00:20:46,578
- Ah…
- I knew it.

435
00:20:46,662 --> 00:20:48,288
The car I saw parked over there was yours.

436
00:20:48,372 --> 00:20:49,414
Wait, wait.

437
00:20:49,498 --> 00:20:51,541
To be honest,
he didn't actually steal me away.

438
00:20:51,625 --> 00:20:53,001
Also, I'm sorry,

439
00:20:53,085 --> 00:20:55,295
- but my friends said
- [Atoy] Ah!

440
00:20:55,379 --> 00:20:56,380
you're terrible at what you do.

441
00:20:56,463 --> 00:20:58,840
So they referred me to Atoy instead.

442
00:20:58,924 --> 00:21:00,634
- [Atoy] Hmm?
- I'm really sorry.

443
00:21:00,717 --> 00:21:01,551
[chuckles]

444
00:21:01,635 --> 00:21:04,137
Anyway, Karla,
kindly assist him at the shop.

445
00:21:04,221 --> 00:21:05,055
- Got it.
- All right.

446
00:21:05,138 --> 00:21:07,349
- I'm really sorry.
- Sir, please,

447
00:21:07,432 --> 00:21:08,308
let's talk this out…

448
00:21:08,392 --> 00:21:09,935
- [titters]
- Tell me.

449
00:21:10,018 --> 00:21:11,019
What? [clicks tongue]

450
00:21:11,103 --> 00:21:14,481
How does it feel
having your client stolen?

451
00:21:14,564 --> 00:21:15,649
So now, you finally know
what it feels like.

452
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:19,027
There's not much I can do
if they come to me.

453
00:21:19,111 --> 00:21:22,114
Maybe they know I'm good at what I do.

454
00:21:22,197 --> 00:21:23,407
I can't say the same for you though.

455
00:21:25,701 --> 00:21:28,036
Atoy, are you saying that
I'm not good at what I do?

456
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:30,080
- Oh! You didn't hear it from me.
- Huh?

457
00:21:30,163 --> 00:21:31,081
Those are your words, not mine.

458
00:21:31,164 --> 00:21:32,708
You're so full of yourself, Atoy!

459
00:21:32,791 --> 00:21:35,377
You steal one client
and suddenly think you're a hotshot!

460
00:21:35,460 --> 00:21:37,587
I'm gonna make you pay… someday.

461
00:21:38,338 --> 00:21:39,923
- [scoffs]
- [funky music playing]

462
00:21:40,007 --> 00:21:41,341
[Emerson] Hi, sir!

463
00:21:41,425 --> 00:21:42,676
- Oh, Emerson.
- Sir Torres! [chuckles]

464
00:21:42,759 --> 00:21:44,094
- How are you doing?
- Good morning.

465
00:21:44,177 --> 00:21:46,346
Um, is there anything
you'd like me to alter?

466
00:21:46,430 --> 00:21:49,141
- What can I do for you?
- Well… I was actually on my way

467
00:21:49,224 --> 00:21:50,142
to Sir Delfin's shop.

468
00:21:50,225 --> 00:21:53,228
I heard the master cutter there
is really good.

469
00:21:53,312 --> 00:21:55,147
I'll go ahead now.

470
00:21:55,647 --> 00:21:57,107
No! That's not true at all!

471
00:21:57,190 --> 00:21:59,067
[funky music continues]

472
00:21:59,943 --> 00:22:01,570
- [Atoy] Thank you.
- Thank you so much, Atoy.

473
00:22:01,653 --> 00:22:02,821
We'll get in touch with you

474
00:22:02,904 --> 00:22:04,906
- once your fitting is ready.
- All right, thank you very much.

475
00:22:04,990 --> 00:22:06,116
- Okay.
- [wind chimes chiming]

476
00:22:07,034 --> 00:22:08,118
OPEN
PLEASE COME IN!

477
00:22:08,201 --> 00:22:12,039
Wow, so many customers.
And so much mess too.

478
00:22:12,122 --> 00:22:13,707
- [chuckles]
- [inhales]

479
00:22:14,583 --> 00:22:15,417
[Cita sighs]

480
00:22:15,500 --> 00:22:16,376
Blame Karla.

481
00:22:16,460 --> 00:22:20,505
I told her to stay here,
but she ran off again.

482
00:22:21,006 --> 00:22:22,382
Just let it slide.

483
00:22:22,466 --> 00:22:24,676
She already has different interests
at this point.

484
00:22:24,760 --> 00:22:26,136
She probably wants to do
something else now.

485
00:22:26,720 --> 00:22:27,888
[grunts]

486
00:22:27,971 --> 00:22:28,805
But hey.

487
00:22:29,765 --> 00:22:31,433
I see we have a lot of orders right now.

488
00:22:31,516 --> 00:22:32,476
[Cita inhales]

489
00:22:32,559 --> 00:22:34,478
Let's get a new assistant.

490
00:22:34,561 --> 00:22:37,606
I agree. I think
I can no longer rely on Karla.

491
00:22:37,689 --> 00:22:39,107
I'm really sorry
for all the trouble, Atoy.

492
00:22:40,484 --> 00:22:41,860
[clicks tongue] It's fine.

493
00:22:41,943 --> 00:22:44,404
[phone ringing]

494
00:22:46,198 --> 00:22:47,074
[beeps]

495
00:22:47,949 --> 00:22:48,867
Hello?

496
00:22:50,160 --> 00:22:51,036
[intriguing music playing]

497
00:22:51,119 --> 00:22:52,454
[in English] I'll be there, sir.

498
00:22:53,789 --> 00:22:54,790
[in English] Copy.

499
00:22:56,792 --> 00:22:58,668
Where are you headed? It's late.

500
00:22:59,169 --> 00:23:00,295
[in English] Special client?

501
00:23:01,046 --> 00:23:01,880
[chuckles]

502
00:23:01,963 --> 00:23:02,798
[in English] Special.

503
00:23:05,175 --> 00:23:06,384
You were incredible earlier!

504
00:23:06,468 --> 00:23:08,386
The handsome guy literally
jumped in just for his wallet.

505
00:23:08,470 --> 00:23:10,180
But you were even more impressive, Ame,

506
00:23:10,263 --> 00:23:11,473
for getting the phone back!

507
00:23:11,556 --> 00:23:14,434
- [giggles]
- [mischievous music playing]

508
00:23:16,061 --> 00:23:18,897
It fell again.
This string is really loose.

509
00:23:21,608 --> 00:23:23,026
- [woman] Ame!
- [mutters] Oh…

510
00:23:23,860 --> 00:23:25,112
What is it?

511
00:23:25,195 --> 00:23:26,196
Did you hear the news?

512
00:23:26,279 --> 00:23:28,281
The guys from the town hall came earlier.

513
00:23:29,074 --> 00:23:30,784
They said the land here
has already been sold.

514
00:23:31,493 --> 00:23:34,538
And we all need to move out
before the end of the month!

515
00:23:35,163 --> 00:23:37,499
- What? But that's not enough time!
- [somber music playing]

516
00:23:37,582 --> 00:23:40,752
I know, but what can we do about it?

517
00:23:41,378 --> 00:23:43,171
We're all just squatters here!

518
00:23:43,672 --> 00:23:45,757
Anyway, I'll go ahead now.

519
00:23:45,841 --> 00:23:48,301
We'll go to the councilor and talk to him.

520
00:23:48,927 --> 00:23:51,263
All right, thank you for letting us know.

521
00:23:51,346 --> 00:23:52,389
Okay.

522
00:23:52,472 --> 00:23:55,308
[somber music playing]

523
00:23:58,603 --> 00:24:00,272
What are we going to do, Ame?

524
00:24:01,398 --> 00:24:02,315
Uh…

525
00:24:02,816 --> 00:24:04,192
Don't worry.

526
00:24:04,276 --> 00:24:05,652
I'll find a way.

527
00:24:07,696 --> 00:24:08,905
Listen, here's what I'll do.

528
00:24:08,989 --> 00:24:11,825
I'll go to Sir John's shop

529
00:24:11,908 --> 00:24:13,827
first thing in the morning tomorrow.

530
00:24:13,910 --> 00:24:15,829
I'll sell the phone to him as well, okay?

531
00:24:15,912 --> 00:24:16,788
I'll go with you!

532
00:24:17,497 --> 00:24:18,498
No need.

533
00:24:18,582 --> 00:24:19,833
You stay here.

534
00:24:20,375 --> 00:24:21,251
Go to sleep.

535
00:24:21,877 --> 00:24:24,462
Otherwise, you'll end up like me,
and never grow up.

536
00:24:25,714 --> 00:24:26,840
- Huh?
- [chuckles]

537
00:24:29,593 --> 00:24:30,552
Bye.

538
00:24:35,849 --> 00:24:40,729
[inquisitive music playing]

539
00:24:47,360 --> 00:24:48,737
[grunts]

540
00:24:51,031 --> 00:24:52,115
[grunts]

541
00:24:52,616 --> 00:24:53,825
[Atoy] Sir!

542
00:24:53,909 --> 00:24:54,951
Captain.

543
00:24:55,660 --> 00:24:59,289
[in English] Thanks for coming
on such short notice.

544
00:25:00,165 --> 00:25:01,208
Anything for you!

545
00:25:01,291 --> 00:25:02,375
[inhales]

546
00:25:02,459 --> 00:25:03,960
This is your next mission.

547
00:25:05,545 --> 00:25:08,757
It was requested by our VIP client.

548
00:25:13,803 --> 00:25:14,846
[Atoy] Hmm.

549
00:25:16,056 --> 00:25:17,599
What happened here, sir?

550
00:25:17,682 --> 00:25:19,309
It was stolen from the farm.

551
00:25:19,809 --> 00:25:21,853
Uh… That rooster is a champion.

552
00:25:21,937 --> 00:25:24,147
In a high-stake derby.

553
00:25:26,483 --> 00:25:27,359
I see.

554
00:25:28,193 --> 00:25:29,694
It is a winning line.

555
00:25:29,778 --> 00:25:30,612
[Ranger] Hmm.

556
00:25:30,695 --> 00:25:32,072
I think they will use it as breed chicken.

557
00:25:32,155 --> 00:25:34,532
For sure. I'll leave it to you then.

558
00:25:34,616 --> 00:25:35,700
Of course, sir.

559
00:25:35,784 --> 00:25:37,327
I'll go through anything,
no matter how hard…

560
00:25:37,911 --> 00:25:40,580
- Just to find it.
- Just to find it.

561
00:25:40,664 --> 00:25:41,706
[chuckles]

562
00:25:41,790 --> 00:25:42,874
Good!

563
00:25:43,375 --> 00:25:47,420
Our client is currently
out of the country.

564
00:25:48,129 --> 00:25:49,089
But when he comes back,

565
00:25:49,673 --> 00:25:51,883
we'll probably set up a meeting.

566
00:25:51,967 --> 00:25:54,594
Hopefully by then,
you already have an update.

567
00:25:55,220 --> 00:25:57,264
Or better yet,
you've already found it by then.

568
00:25:57,889 --> 00:25:59,182
[in English] Consider it done, sir.

569
00:25:59,891 --> 00:26:02,227
[stirring music playing]

570
00:26:03,853 --> 00:26:05,313
[man] Oh.

571
00:26:05,397 --> 00:26:06,690
Thank you, sir.

572
00:26:06,773 --> 00:26:09,943
Uh, Sir John, can I borrow
some money from you?

573
00:26:10,944 --> 00:26:11,987
Sure thing, anything for you.

574
00:26:12,070 --> 00:26:13,571
We've known each other
for a long time anyway.

575
00:26:13,655 --> 00:26:15,031
How much do you need? Three thousand?

576
00:26:15,740 --> 00:26:18,034
Uh, I was hoping for around 20,000.

577
00:26:18,118 --> 00:26:19,744
What? That's quite a lot!

578
00:26:19,828 --> 00:26:23,832
Well, we really need
to find a new place to stay,

579
00:26:23,915 --> 00:26:26,918
and everyone these days is asking
for advance payments and deposits.

580
00:26:27,002 --> 00:26:28,878
- [woman] Um, miss?
- [John mutters]

581
00:26:29,379 --> 00:26:31,047
I know a side job.

582
00:26:31,131 --> 00:26:32,882
It pays 1,000 per night.

583
00:26:32,966 --> 00:26:34,801
In just ten nights, that's already 10,000.

584
00:26:35,385 --> 00:26:36,928
And you could even earn more.

585
00:26:37,012 --> 00:26:40,098
Around five to 10,000 per night.

586
00:26:40,181 --> 00:26:41,766
Hold on. Who are you?

587
00:26:41,850 --> 00:26:45,103
That's Bebang. She's a talent manager.

588
00:26:45,186 --> 00:26:46,021
[scoffs]

589
00:26:46,604 --> 00:26:49,190
What kind of talent manager
are you exactly?

590
00:26:49,274 --> 00:26:50,817
Why is the pay so high?

591
00:26:52,319 --> 00:26:54,446
Come with me. I'll show you.

592
00:26:55,947 --> 00:26:57,782
If you can't even explain
what you do, then forget it.

593
00:26:58,742 --> 00:27:00,201
Just come with me.

594
00:27:00,285 --> 00:27:01,953
This will be easy for you.

595
00:27:02,620 --> 00:27:04,748
Hey. Quit forcing me!

596
00:27:05,498 --> 00:27:08,877
[menacing music playing]

597
00:27:14,299 --> 00:27:16,009
That woman, I can't believe
she's pushing me.

598
00:27:16,092 --> 00:27:18,136
She might drag me somewhere dangerous.

599
00:27:18,219 --> 00:27:19,471
‪[dog barking in distance]

600
00:27:25,602 --> 00:27:30,065
[mischievous music playing]

601
00:27:37,697 --> 00:27:41,576
- [muffled grunting]
- [suspenseful music playing]

602
00:27:41,659 --> 00:27:45,747
[electronic blipping]

603
00:27:45,830 --> 00:27:49,292
[intense music playing]

604
00:27:51,461 --> 00:27:52,587
I'm looking for someone.

605
00:27:52,670 --> 00:27:53,671
- Her name is Ibyang… a kid…
- There's Ibyang!

606
00:27:53,755 --> 00:27:54,672
Do you know that kid?

607
00:27:54,756 --> 00:27:55,965
[woman] She's up
on the roof of the house!

608
00:27:56,049 --> 00:27:58,134
- There she is!
- Help!

609
00:27:58,218 --> 00:27:59,052
- [explosion]
- [shrieks]

610
00:27:59,135 --> 00:28:02,013
She really is an orphan now. Poor Ibyang.

611
00:28:02,097 --> 00:28:05,183
Amy is the only one she has left,
and now she's gone missing.

612
00:28:05,266 --> 00:28:06,142
Miss Cita!

613
00:28:06,226 --> 00:28:07,644
- [intriguing music playing]
- [gasps]

614
00:28:07,727 --> 00:28:08,812
You pervert!

615
00:28:08,895 --> 00:28:10,355
UP NEXT

616
00:28:10,980 --> 00:28:12,774
TTH!

617
00:28:12,857 --> 00:28:15,276
What's behind that door?

618
00:28:15,360 --> 00:28:16,653
It looks really interesting.

619
00:28:17,195 --> 00:28:19,739
There seems to be some kind
of unusual show happening there.

620
00:28:20,323 --> 00:28:23,201
[in English] It's very entertaining
yet violent.

621
00:28:23,284 --> 00:28:24,327
[man] Why are you here?

622
00:28:24,411 --> 00:28:26,621
[grunts]

623
00:28:29,833 --> 00:28:31,334
[grunting]

624
00:28:33,128 --> 00:28:34,212
[gun cocks]

625
00:28:38,425 --> 00:28:40,677
Subtitle translation by:
Inocencio Cañete Raman Jr.
